I c... I can't.

13
00:02:51.423 --> 00:02:53.658
Push!

14
00:02:56.373 --> 00:02:59.644
The head!

15
00:03:11.136 --> 00:03:12.708
A boy. Princess.

16
00:03:12.793 --> 00:03:15.255
Praise the Mother!

17
00:03:25.625 --> 00:03:26.826
Ahh.

18
00:03:28.328 --> 00:03:29.395
Healthy?

19
00:03:29.480 --> 00:03:31.311
Kicking like
a goat. Princess.

20
00:03:46.215 --> 00:03:48.394
Princess...

21
00:03:48.855 --> 00:03:52.065
the Queen has requested that
the child be brought to her...

22
00:03:52.331 --> 00:03:53.926
immediately.

23
00:03:56.712 --> 00:03:57.746
Why?

24
00:04:07.981 --> 00:04:09.458
I'll take him myself.

25
00:04:09.543 --> 00:04:11.094
You should remain
abed. Princess...

26
00:04:11.179 --> 00:04:13.414
Yes. I should!
Help me dress.

27
00:04:21.861 --> 00:04:23.563
Ooh...

28
00:04:28.224 --> 00:04:29.725
Mmm...

29
00:04:30.493 --> 00:04:31.895
Princess...

30
00:04:33.288 --> 00:04:34.691
your dress?

31
00:05:07.879 --> 00:05:09.911
- Mm. mm. mm. mm. mm.
- Princess?

32
00:05:09.996 --> 00:05:12.011
- Oh. it's coming.
- The afterbirth!

33
00:05:22.508 --> 00:05:24.660
A boy. I've just heard.

34
00:05:24.744 --> 00:05:26.668
- Yes.
- Well done.

35
00:05:27.747 --> 00:05:30.730
- Where are you going?
- She wants to see him.

36
00:05:30.815 --> 00:05:32.121
Now?

37
00:05:33.252 --> 00:05:34.369
I'm coming with you.

38
00:05:34.453 --> 00:05:36.333
- I should hope so.
- Let me take him.

39
00:05:36.418 --> 00:05:38.353
No. she'll get no such
satisfaction from me.

40
00:05:38.438 --> 00:05:40.840
Just take my arm.
at the least.

41
00:05:45.284 --> 00:05:47.319
Was it terribly painful?

42
00:05:48.824 --> 00:05:49.942
Oh gods.

43
00:05:54.840 --> 00:05:57.243
I took a lance through
the shoulder once.

44
00:05:58.044 --> 00:05:59.795
My deepest sympathies.

45
00:05:59.956 --> 00:06:02.059
The Princess...
The Princess...

46
00:06:02.144 --> 00:06:03.899
I am glad
I am not a woman.

47
00:06:03.983 --> 00:06:06.919
- My Princess...
- My Lord...

48
00:06:11.974 --> 00:06:13.840
What is it?

49
00:06:14.353 --> 00:06:16.088
What is it?
What is it?

50
00:06:16.595 --> 00:06:17.830
Fuck.

51
00:06:18.364 --> 00:06:20.933
Walk... Walk!

52
00:06:25.838 --> 00:06:28.074
What could she
possibly want?

53
00:06:29.742 --> 00:06:31.677
I thought we
were past this.

54
00:06:36.015 --> 00:06:38.800
Princess. Ser Laenor.
it is a privilege

55
00:06:38.884 --> 00:06:40.769
to be amongst the first
to congratulate you.

56
00:06:40.853 --> 00:06:42.838
Thank you.
Lord Caswell.

57
00:06:42.922 --> 00:06:45.874
If I may be of any service.

58
00:06:45.958 --> 00:06:48.360
The day may yet come. my Lord.

59
00:06:55.701 --> 00:06:57.786
We are turning back.
all right?

60
00:06:57.870 --> 00:07:00.188
She can come to us.
all right?

61
00:07:00.272 --> 00:07:03.709
No. Not unless you wish to
carry me down those fucking stairs.

62
00:07:21.193 --> 00:07:22.644
This is absurd.

63
00:07:23.024 --> 00:07:24.426
Mm...

64
00:07:39.612 --> 00:07:41.013
Princess.

65
00:07:58.584 --> 00:08:03.231
Rhaenyra! You should
be resting after your labors.

66
00:08:03.969 --> 00:08:06.788
I have no doubt that you
would prefer that. Your Grace.

67
00:08:06.872 --> 00:08:08.223
You must sit.

68
00:08:08.307 --> 00:08:10.726
Talya. fetch a cushion
for the Princess.

69
00:08:10.810 --> 00:08:14.196
- There's no need.
- Nonsense.

70
00:08:14.280 --> 00:08:16.015
We'll finish this later.

71
00:08:17.383 --> 00:08:18.784
Your Grace.

72
00:08:24.089 --> 00:08:26.775
What happy news this morning.

73
00:08:26.859 --> 00:08:28.793
Indeed. Your Grace.

74
00:08:29.301 --> 00:08:30.707
Where is he?

75
00:08:31.481 --> 00:08:34.683
Where is my grandson?
There.

76
00:08:36.372 --> 00:08:38.107
There he is.

77
00:08:38.737 --> 00:08:40.139
Oh.

78
00:08:41.674 --> 00:08:43.409
A fine Prince.

79
00:08:44.076 --> 00:08:45.694
Sturdy.

80
00:08:45.778 --> 00:08:48.230
You will make
a fearsome knight.

81
00:08:48.681 --> 00:08:50.132
Yes. you will.

82
00:08:50.216 --> 00:08:52.121
Does the babe
have a name yet?

83
00:08:52.685 --> 00:08:54.420
- We haven't spoken...
- Joffrey.

84
00:08:55.454 --> 00:08:57.005
He'll be called Joffrey.

85
00:08:57.089 --> 00:08:59.629
That's an unusual name
for a Velaryon.

86
00:09:01.827 --> 00:09:04.146
I do believe he has
his father's nose.

87
00:09:06.398 --> 00:09:08.033
Don't you?

88
00:09:11.537 --> 00:09:14.489
If you
don't mind. Your Grace.

89
00:09:14.574 --> 00:09:17.726
your daughter has exerted
herself heroically and should rest.

90
00:09:17.810 --> 00:09:19.211
Of course.

91
00:09:21.247 --> 00:09:22.281
There.

92
00:09:31.357 --> 00:09:33.092
Well done. my girl.

93
00:09:35.127 --> 00:09:37.613
I do hope the labor was easy.

94
00:09:38.130 --> 00:09:41.121
I think I called
the midwife a cunt.

95
00:09:41.331 --> 00:09:42.366
Oh.

96
00:09:49.074 --> 00:09:51.621
Do keep trying. Ser Laenor.

97
00:09:52.044 --> 00:09:54.980
Soon or late. you may
get one who looks like you.

98
00:10:08.961 --> 00:10:11.079
You don't...
think to consult me

99
00:10:11.163 --> 00:10:13.048
before you name my child?

100
00:10:13.132 --> 00:10:15.367
He's our child.
is he not?

101
00:10:16.902 --> 00:10:18.687
Only one of us is bleeding.

102
00:10:18.771 --> 00:10:22.657
I deserve some say in
the affairs of my own family.

103
00:10:22.741 --> 00:10:25.878
You haven't seemed so
interested in our affairs of late.

104
00:10:38.090 --> 00:10:41.660
And he sees a big. scary dragon!

105
00:10:46.632 --> 00:10:48.191
Mother...

106
00:10:48.279 --> 00:10:49.480
look.

107
00:10:54.606 --> 00:10:58.093
- We chose an egg for the baby.
- Ahh.

108
00:10:58.177 --> 00:11:00.462
That looks like the perfect one.

109
00:11:00.546 --> 00:11:03.465
- I let Luke choose.
- Thank you. Jace.

110
00:11:03.549 --> 00:11:06.169
Not every day an egg leaves
the Dragon pit. Princess.

111
00:11:06.254 --> 00:11:09.491
I thought it best
to escort the lads.

112
00:11:10.809 --> 00:11:13.211
Laenor and I thank you.
Commander.

113
00:11:14.212 --> 00:11:16.348
Another boy. I heard.

114
00:11:21.143 --> 00:11:23.662
What a fine knight you
are going to make. eh?

115
00:11:24.192 --> 00:11:25.860
Might I?

116
00:11:27.025 --> 00:11:30.128
Ser Harwin wishes to be
introduced to Joffrey.

117
00:11:32.613 --> 00:11:33.800
Of course.

118
00:11:35.043 --> 00:11:37.285
- Joffrey. is it?
- Mm-hm.

119
00:11:37.369 --> 00:11:38.403
Mm.

120
00:11:44.476 --> 00:11:46.894
Father. please
may I hold Joffrey?

121
00:11:46.978 --> 00:11:49.096
- No. no. No.
- Ah. ah. ah. ah. ah. ah.

122
00:11:49.180 --> 00:11:51.481
Back to the Dragon pit
for you two.

123
00:11:51.566 --> 00:11:52.595
Come on!

124
00:11:52.680 --> 00:11:54.917
Before they
send out a search party.

125
00:12:05.730 --> 00:12:09.167
You're asleep in front of the
Commander of the City Watch.

126
00:12:10.735 --> 00:12:12.353
Terrible lack of respect.

127
00:12:12.437 --> 00:12:16.374
A certain insolence runs
in the family. I'm afraid.

128
00:13:07.725 --> 00:13:09.577
Call Vermax
to heel. Prince Jacaerys.

129
00:13:09.661 --> 00:13:11.396
<i>Speaking High Valyrian...</i>

130
00:13:45.864 --> 00:13:46.864
Vermax!

131
00:13:47.699 --> 00:13:48.700
Vermax!

132
00:13:52.170 --> 00:13:56.157
Zaldrizo
aoho syt aeksio sagon ao bevilza.

133
00:13:56.241 --> 00:13:57.658
darilaros nuhys...

134
00:13:57.742 --> 00:13:59.560
You must hold mastery over
your dragon. my young Princes.

135
00:13:59.644 --> 00:14:02.730
...hae Darilarot
Aegot Vvsperzomy.

136
00:14:02.814 --> 00:14:04.732
As Prince
Aegon has with Sunfyre.

137
00:14:04.816 --> 00:14:07.935
Zijosy aot tetiri ozlettosy.

138
00:14:08.019 --> 00:14:12.106
toli rybagon zirylo vindilza.

139
00:14:12.190 --> 00:14:13.607
Once they're fully bound to you.
they will refuse

140
00:14:13.691 --> 00:14:15.910
to take instruction
from any other.

141
00:14:19.998 --> 00:14:22.233
- Can I say it?
- Mm-hm.

142
00:14:28.773 --> 00:14:30.575
Dracarys. Vermax!

143
00:14:53.298 --> 00:14:56.817
Aemond. we have
a surprise for you.

144
00:14:56.901 --> 00:14:59.204
- What is it?
- Something very special.

145
00:15:00.672 --> 00:15:02.923
You're the only one
of us without a dragon.

146
00:15:03.007 --> 00:15:03.858
Indeed.

147
00:15:03.942 --> 00:15:06.660
And we felt badly about it.

148
00:15:06.744 --> 00:15:09.663
so we found one for you.

149
00:15:09.747 --> 00:15:12.633
A dragon? How?

150
00:15:12.717 --> 00:15:14.719
The gods provide.

151
00:15:22.594 --> 00:15:25.513
- Behold...
- The Pink Dread!

152
00:15:28.333 --> 00:15:29.783
Be sure to mount her carefully.

153
00:15:29.867 --> 00:15:31.719
First flight's always rough.

154
00:17:08.333 --> 00:17:11.085
This one has 60 rings...

155
00:17:11.169 --> 00:17:13.821
and two pairs of legs on each.

156
00:17:13.905 --> 00:17:15.640
That's 240.

157
00:17:16.741 --> 00:17:18.309
Yes. it is.

158
00:17:20.378 --> 00:17:22.313
It has eyes...

159
00:17:22.947 --> 00:17:24.465
though...

160
00:17:24.549 --> 00:17:27.468
I don't believe it can see.

161
00:17:27.552 --> 00:17:29.954
And why is that so.
do you think?

162
00:17:31.756 --> 00:17:33.991
It is beyond
our understanding.

163
00:17:35.793 --> 00:17:39.179
I suppose you're right.
Some things just are.

164
00:17:42.600 --> 00:17:44.535
Your Grace.

165
00:17:45.236 --> 00:17:47.321
Aemond.

166
00:17:47.405 --> 00:17:48.922
- What have you done?
- He did it again.

167
00:17:49.006 --> 00:17:50.457
After how many
times you've been warned.

168
00:17:50.541 --> 00:17:51.859
must I have you confined
to your chambers?!

169
00:17:51.943 --> 00:17:53.727
- They made me do it!
- As if you needed encouragement.

170
00:17:53.811 --> 00:17:55.062
Your obsession
with those beasts

171
00:17:55.146 --> 00:17:56.163
goes beyond understanding.

172
00:17:56.247 --> 00:17:57.682
They gave me a pig!

173
00:17:58.249 --> 00:17:59.233
A what?

174
00:17:59.317 --> 00:18:00.768
They said they found
a dragon for me.

175
00:18:00.852 --> 00:18:03.203
The last ring
has no legs at all.

176
00:18:03.287 --> 00:18:05.172
But it was a pig.

177
00:18:05.256 --> 00:18:07.775
You will have
a dragon one day.

178
00:18:07.859 --> 00:18:11.529
- He'll have to close an eye.
- I know it.

179
00:18:12.296 --> 00:18:14.031
They all laughed.

180
00:18:17.535 --> 00:18:20.554
They made wings
for it. apparently. and a tail.

181
00:18:20.638 --> 00:18:22.356
The lad shouldn't
have been so credulous.

182
00:18:22.440 --> 00:18:23.457
He's a child.

183
00:18:23.541 --> 00:18:24.992
He thought
they'd happened upon

184
00:18:25.076 --> 00:18:26.627
some wild unnamed dragon

185
00:18:26.711 --> 00:18:28.195
and lured it to the Dragon pit?

186
00:18:28.279 --> 00:18:29.697
Your grandsons
are a menace.

187
00:18:29.781 --> 00:18:31.532
They're more children
than he is.

188
00:18:31.616 --> 00:18:35.019
Th-They're savages.
And it's not surprising.

189
00:18:36.788 --> 00:18:40.024
Are you sure it wasn't our
Aegon who put them up to it?

190
00:18:43.694 --> 00:18:45.930
It's a wonder to me
their eggs ever hatched.

191
00:18:47.265 --> 00:18:49.283
- And why is that?
- You know why.

192
00:18:49.367 --> 00:18:52.252
- I'm afraid I don't.
- Don't!

193
00:18:52.336 --> 00:18:54.071
Viserys.

194
00:18:56.541 --> 00:18:58.943
We shall continue
this afternoon. Eddard.

195
00:19:07.285 --> 00:19:09.737
I have raised
this matter before

196
00:19:09.821 --> 00:19:12.690
and you forbade me to
speak of it. so I held my tongue.

197
00:19:14.325 --> 00:19:16.977
To have one child
like that is a mistake.

198
00:19:17.061 --> 00:19:19.513
to have three is an insult.

199
00:19:19.597 --> 00:19:21.281
to the throne. to you.

200
00:19:21.365 --> 00:19:24.551
to House Velaryon and the match
you battled so hard to make for her.

201
00:19:24.635 --> 00:19:27.572
Not to mention
decency itself.

202
00:19:28.439 --> 00:19:30.675
I had a black mare once.

203
00:19:31.309 --> 00:19:33.060
Black like a raven.

204
00:19:33.144 --> 00:19:35.729
One day.
she escaped her pasture

205
00:19:35.813 --> 00:19:38.749
and the neighboring stallion
sired a foal on her.

206
00:19:40.718 --> 00:19:44.838
The stallion was as silver as
the moon on a winter's night

207
00:19:44.922 --> 00:19:47.641
and the foal.
when it was born.

208
00:19:47.725 --> 00:19:50.444
chestnut.

209
00:19:50.528 --> 00:19:54.932
Just the most unremarkable
brown horse you ever saw.

210
00:19:56.534 --> 00:19:59.470
Nature is a thing
of mysterious works.

211
00:20:05.409 --> 00:20:06.911
How do you know?

212
00:20:08.579 --> 00:20:10.697
The silver stallion.

213
00:20:10.781 --> 00:20:12.550
How do you know it was him?

214
00:20:14.318 --> 00:20:15.969
Did you witness the act itself?

215
00:20:20.224 --> 00:20:22.342
The consequences

216
00:20:22.426 --> 00:20:25.813
of an allegation
like the one you toy at

217
00:20:25.897 --> 00:20:27.632
would be dire.

218
00:20:35.439 --> 00:20:37.842
Do not speak of this again.

219
00:20:47.985 --> 00:20:50.404
Have I lost
my sanity. Ser Criston?

220
00:20:50.488 --> 00:20:51.505
Do my senses
lead me astray?

221
00:20:51.589 --> 00:20:52.606
Or is everyone else asleep.

222
00:20:52.690 --> 00:20:54.441
dreaming the same
woolly dream?

223
00:20:54.525 --> 00:20:56.761
Sometimes seems so.
Your Grace.

224
00:20:59.030 --> 00:21:01.181
She flaunts the privilege of
her inheritance without shame.

225
00:21:01.265 --> 00:21:03.383
She expects everyone in
the Red Keep to deny the truth

226
00:21:03.467 --> 00:21:04.718
our eyes can all plainly see.

227
00:21:04.802 --> 00:21:06.253
- And the King. her father...
- He knows.

228
00:21:06.337 --> 00:21:07.721
Of course. he knows.
Or did once.

229
00:21:07.805 --> 00:21:08.889
but has convinced
himself otherwise.

230
00:21:08.973 --> 00:21:11.725
He'll do naught
but make excuses for her.

231
00:21:11.809 --> 00:21:15.496
The Princess Rhaenyra
is brazen and relentless.

232
00:21:15.580 --> 00:21:19.600
A spider who stings
and sucks her prey dry.

233
00:21:19.684 --> 00:21:21.919
A spoiled cunt.

234
00:21:26.958 --> 00:21:29.760
That was beneath me.
Your Grace. I apologize.

235
00:21:32.997 --> 00:21:34.615
I have to believe.

236
00:21:34.699 --> 00:21:39.386
that in the end. honor
and decency will prevail.

237
00:21:39.470 --> 00:21:43.323
We need to hew to that
and to each other.

238
00:22:01.559 --> 00:22:04.061
- Whose idea was it?
- Oh!

239
00:22:08.299 --> 00:22:09.750
The pig.

240
00:22:09.834 --> 00:22:13.153
- Was it your plot?
- No...

241
00:22:13.237 --> 00:22:15.088
it was Jace

242
00:22:15.172 --> 00:22:17.391
and... uh...

243
00:22:17.475 --> 00:22:19.326
it-it was the two of them.

244
00:22:19.410 --> 00:22:21.094
I couldn't be sure.

245
00:22:21.178 --> 00:22:22.496
Aemond is your brother.

246
00:22:22.580 --> 00:22:24.665
- Well. he's a twat.
- We are family.

247
00:22:24.749 --> 00:22:27.000
You may cuff him about
as you wish at home.

248
00:22:27.084 --> 00:22:30.370
but in the world...
we must defend our own.

249
00:22:30.454 --> 00:22:31.505
It was funny.

250
00:22:31.589 --> 00:22:32.673
Do you think
Rhaenyra's sons

251
00:22:32.757 --> 00:22:34.692
will be your
playthings forever?

252
00:22:36.025 --> 00:22:37.710
As things stand...

253
00:22:38.029 --> 00:22:39.146
Rhaenyra will ascend the throne

254
00:22:39.230 --> 00:22:42.416
and Jacaerys Targaryen
will be her heir.

255
00:22:42.500 --> 00:22:44.952
- So?
- Ugh! You are nearly a man-grown.

256
00:22:45.036 --> 00:22:47.371
How is it that you can be
so shortsighted?

257
00:22:49.907 --> 00:22:52.526
If Rhaenyra comes
into power...

258
00:22:52.610 --> 00:22:55.346
your very life could be forfeit.

259
00:22:56.380 --> 00:22:58.432
Aemond's as well.

260
00:22:58.516 --> 00:23:02.135
She could move to cut off any
challenge to her succession.

261
00:23:02.219 --> 00:23:04.237
- Then I won't challenge...
- You are the challenge!

262
00:23:04.321 --> 00:23:05.706
You are the challenge.
Aegon!

263
00:23:05.790 --> 00:23:08.726
Simply by living
and breathing!

264
00:23:12.830 --> 00:23:15.782
You are the King's
firstborn son...

265
00:23:15.866 --> 00:23:18.685
and what they know. what
everyone in the realm knows

266
00:23:18.769 --> 00:23:21.822
in their blood
and in their bones...

267
00:23:21.906 --> 00:23:25.142
is that one day.
you will be our King.

268
00:23:34.085 --> 00:23:35.119
Get dressed.

269
00:24:30.641 --> 00:24:32.359
Dracarys!

270
00:25:00.037 --> 00:25:02.355
The lamb hearts are excellent.

271
00:25:02.439 --> 00:25:05.225
We are fortunate in our
cook. Your Excellence.

272
00:25:05.309 --> 00:25:06.727
There's a plum-cake
yet to be served.

273
00:25:06.811 --> 00:25:08.762
which will have us
fighting over the crumbs.

274
00:25:08.846 --> 00:25:10.831
Then before we come to blows...

275
00:25:12.283 --> 00:25:16.169
A toast to Aegon the Conqueror.
your exalted forebear.

276
00:25:16.253 --> 00:25:18.638
who joined our cause
against Volantis

277
00:25:18.722 --> 00:25:20.140
in the Century of Blood.

278
00:25:20.224 --> 00:25:23.610
On the great dragon Balerion.
he flew to our aid in Lys

279
00:25:23.694 --> 00:25:25.579
and burned a fleet
of enemy ships.

280
00:25:25.663 --> 00:25:27.398
thus turning the tide.

281
00:25:29.333 --> 00:25:32.269
- Aegon the Conqueror.
- To Aegon.

282
00:25:35.206 --> 00:25:37.824
This brings
me to some business.

283
00:25:37.908 --> 00:25:40.026
A proposal I wish to make

284
00:25:40.110 --> 00:25:42.963
in the spirit of honoring
our storied alliance.

285
00:25:43.047 --> 00:25:45.465
If your aim is to marry one of
our daughters. Your Excellence.

286
00:25:45.549 --> 00:25:48.068
you might have said so and
spared us the history lesson.

287
00:25:48.152 --> 00:25:50.003
What?

288
00:25:50.087 --> 00:25:53.406
I would not count myself
so deserving. my Lady Laena.

289
00:25:55.726 --> 00:26:00.213
I wish to offer you a permanent
residence here in Pentos.

290
00:26:00.297 --> 00:26:02.816
This manse I would
gift to you. outright.

291
00:26:02.900 --> 00:26:05.318
along with its
farms and lands.

292
00:26:05.402 --> 00:26:06.953
the vineyard and the wood.

293
00:26:07.037 --> 00:26:09.122
The tenants would pay
their tributes annually

294
00:26:09.206 --> 00:26:11.291
to their new Targaryen lord.

295
00:26:11.375 --> 00:26:13.960
You would have your freedom
of the city and the harbor.

296
00:26:14.044 --> 00:26:17.147
as befits your royal station.

297
00:26:20.217 --> 00:26:21.301
Continue.

298
00:26:21.385 --> 00:26:24.805
Lys and its allies rise again.

299
00:26:24.889 --> 00:26:27.374
The Triarchy has
made common cause

300
00:26:27.458 --> 00:26:29.309
with Qoren Martell of Dorne.

301
00:26:29.393 --> 00:26:32.612
At any moment. they may
turn their sights north.

302
00:26:32.696 --> 00:26:35.015
Your family has dragons.

303
00:26:35.099 --> 00:26:39.886
Three now...
mayhaps four in the future.

304
00:26:39.970 --> 00:26:41.621
My aim is to protect Pentos

305
00:26:41.705 --> 00:26:43.824
from the lustful eye
of the Triarchy.

306
00:26:43.908 --> 00:26:48.094
Aid Pentos in this.
as Aegon once did...

307
00:26:48.178 --> 00:26:52.499
and my gratitude will fill
your cup and overflow it.

308
00:26:52.583 --> 00:26:54.801
Your Excellence.
we are travelers.

309
00:26:54.885 --> 00:26:57.621
We've already extended
our visit here.

310
00:27:01.892 --> 00:27:04.177
It's a most generous offer.

311
00:27:04.261 --> 00:27:06.497
And one we will
certainly entertain.

312
00:27:36.660 --> 00:27:40.597
- You are considering Prince Reggio's offer.
- We have a good life here.

313
00:27:41.632 --> 00:27:43.783
We're free to do
as we please.

314
00:27:43.867 --> 00:27:44.951
welcomed and feted.

315
00:27:45.035 --> 00:27:47.254
- And eternally guests.
- Precisely.

316
00:27:47.338 --> 00:27:50.290
We are without responsibility.
The political scheming.

317
00:27:50.374 --> 00:27:53.293
the endless shifting
of loyalties and succession

318
00:27:53.377 --> 00:27:55.295
is none of ours.

319
00:27:55.379 --> 00:27:58.615
- They are using us.
- It's refreshing. isn't it?

320
00:27:59.950 --> 00:28:01.601
A simple transaction.

321
00:28:01.685 --> 00:28:04.421
We have dragons.
they have gold.

322
00:28:09.360 --> 00:28:11.244
We are more than this. Daemon.

323
00:28:11.328 --> 00:28:12.779
We are not minstrels
or mummers

324
00:28:12.863 --> 00:28:14.314
who play at the pleasure
of an alien prince.

325
00:28:14.398 --> 00:28:17.167
We are the blood
of Old Valyria.

326
00:28:17.935 --> 00:28:19.386
We don't belong here.

327
00:28:19.470 --> 00:28:22.406
Valyria is gone.
We don't belong anywhere.

328
00:28:27.878 --> 00:28:30.163
I want my child to be born

329
00:28:30.247 --> 00:28:32.599
where I was born.
on Driftmark.

330
00:28:32.683 --> 00:28:33.700
in my lord father's castle.

331
00:28:33.784 --> 00:28:36.603
I want my daughters to be
raised in their homeland

332
00:28:36.687 --> 00:28:37.971
with their family

333
00:28:38.055 --> 00:28:40.991
according to
their birthright.

334
00:28:42.593 --> 00:28:46.146
And at my end. I want to die
a dragonrider's death.

335
00:28:46.230 --> 00:28:49.166
Not that of some
fat country lord.

336
00:29:21.865 --> 00:29:24.417
Soften your knees.

337
00:29:24.501 --> 00:29:25.685
Feet light.

338
00:29:25.769 --> 00:29:28.188
Keep your feet
light and your hands heavy.

339
00:29:28.272 --> 00:29:30.890
This is the stuff. Lyonel.

340
00:29:30.974 --> 00:29:32.826
Lads that learn together.

341
00:29:32.910 --> 00:29:34.294
train together...

342
00:29:34.378 --> 00:29:37.263
knock each other down.
pick each other up.

343
00:29:37.347 --> 00:29:40.900
They will certainly form a
lifelong bond. wouldn't you agree?

344
00:29:40.984 --> 00:29:42.553
That is the hope. Your Grace.

345
00:29:45.222 --> 00:29:46.740
Don't stand too upright.
my Prince.

346
00:29:46.824 --> 00:29:48.158
You'll get knocked down.

347
00:29:59.036 --> 00:30:00.270
Aegon.

348
00:30:01.872 --> 00:30:03.790
I've won my first bout.
Ser Criston.

349
00:30:03.874 --> 00:30:06.393
My opponent sues for mercy.

350
00:30:06.477 --> 00:30:09.763
Well. you'll have a new opponent
then. My Lord of the Straw.

351
00:30:09.847 --> 00:30:11.582
Let's see if you
can touch me.

352
00:30:12.282 --> 00:30:14.051
You and your brother.

353
00:30:41.445 --> 00:30:42.929
You're gonna have
to do better than that.

354
00:30:47.451 --> 00:30:48.668
Ah.

355
00:30:48.752 --> 00:30:49.736
Weapons up. boys.

356
00:30:49.820 --> 00:30:52.122
Give your enemies
no quarter.

357
00:30:54.324 --> 00:30:56.276
It seems the younger boys
could do better with a bit

358
00:30:56.360 --> 00:30:59.245
of your attention...
Ser Criston.

359
00:30:59.329 --> 00:31:02.048
You question my method
of instruction. ser?

360
00:31:02.132 --> 00:31:06.436
Oh. I merely suggest that
method be applied to all your pupils.

361
00:31:09.706 --> 00:31:10.741
Very well.

362
00:31:14.144 --> 00:31:15.995
Jacaerys... come here.

363
00:31:16.079 --> 00:31:17.564
You spar with Aegon.

364
00:31:20.851 --> 00:31:22.586
Eldest son against eldest son.

365
00:31:25.088 --> 00:31:27.640
- It's hardly a fair match.
- I know you've never seen true battle. ser.

366
00:31:27.724 --> 00:31:31.228
but when steel is drawn. a fair match
isn't something anyone should expect.

367
00:31:33.797 --> 00:31:34.831
Blades up.

368
00:31:36.166 --> 00:31:38.268
Engage.

369
00:31:43.574 --> 00:31:45.309
Ow.

370
00:32:01.558 --> 00:32:03.794
- Foul play.
- I'll deal with him.

371
00:32:06.263 --> 00:32:09.649
Plant your feet. You have a height
advantage. Use it. Advance on him...

372
00:32:15.272 --> 00:32:16.956
You!

373
00:32:17.040 --> 00:32:19.926
Close with him.

374
00:32:20.010 --> 00:32:21.261
Press him backward!

375
00:32:21.345 --> 00:32:22.562
Close with him!

376
00:32:22.646 --> 00:32:25.165
Stay on the attack!
Use your feet!

377
00:32:27.951 --> 00:32:29.353
Don't let him get up.

378
00:32:31.755 --> 00:32:32.956
Stay on the attack!

379
00:32:34.258 --> 00:32:35.575
Enough!

380
00:32:37.027 --> 00:32:39.712
- You dare put hands on me?
- Aegon!

381
00:32:39.796 --> 00:32:41.881
You forget yourself. Strong.
That is the Prince.

382
00:32:41.965 --> 00:32:43.700
This is what you teach. Cole?

383
00:32:46.103 --> 00:32:47.504
Cruelty...

384
00:32:48.272 --> 00:32:50.207
to the weaker opponent?

385
00:32:52.409 --> 00:32:54.260
Your interest
in the princeling's training

386
00:32:54.344 --> 00:32:56.647
is quite unusual. Commander.

387
00:32:57.814 --> 00:32:59.866
Most men would only
have that kind of devotion

388
00:32:59.950 --> 00:33:01.518
toward a cousin...

389
00:33:03.086 --> 00:33:04.488
or a brother...

390
00:33:05.188 --> 00:33:06.423
or a son.

391
00:33:23.240 --> 00:33:24.824
Get back!

392
00:33:24.908 --> 00:33:26.643
Say it again!

393
00:33:27.244 --> 00:33:28.528
Say it again!

394
00:33:28.612 --> 00:33:30.847
Thought as much.

395
00:33:33.817 --> 00:33:35.468
Let him be bathed with a cloth.

396
00:33:35.552 --> 00:33:37.303
and see to it the cook

397
00:33:37.387 --> 00:33:39.790
gives you a good.
clear wine to drink.

398
00:33:41.892 --> 00:33:43.543
Princess...

399
00:33:43.627 --> 00:33:47.030
there's been an incident
in the yard.

400
00:33:56.106 --> 00:33:58.524
It fills me
with unrelenting shame.

401
00:33:58.608 --> 00:34:00.827
So that's
what this is about then?

402
00:34:00.911 --> 00:34:04.430
- Your shame.
- Our shame. Harwin!

403
00:34:04.514 --> 00:34:05.999
Shame on the whole
of House Strong.

404
00:34:06.083 --> 00:34:08.968
Because I laid my
hands on that insufferable Cole.

405
00:34:09.052 --> 00:34:11.537
- the son of a steward?
- He is a Knight of the Kings guard now.

406
00:34:11.621 --> 00:34:13.473
- a defender of the crown.
- He assailed Prince Jacaerys.

407
00:34:13.557 --> 00:34:15.692
the future heir to the throne.

408
00:34:17.461 --> 00:34:21.781
You have laid
us open to accusations

409
00:34:21.865 --> 00:34:23.449
of an uglier treachery.

410
00:34:23.533 --> 00:34:25.902
And what treachery is that?

411
00:34:28.271 --> 00:34:30.674
Don't play the fool
with me. boy.

412
00:34:31.875 --> 00:34:35.194
Your intimacy with
the Princess Rhaenyra

413
00:34:35.278 --> 00:34:38.598
is an offense that would
mean exile and death...

414
00:34:38.682 --> 00:34:43.369
for you. for her.
for the children!

415
00:34:43.453 --> 00:34:46.390
It is rumor only...

416
00:34:47.691 --> 00:34:49.175
spun by the Princess's rivals.

417
00:34:49.259 --> 00:34:51.628
People have eyes. boy.

418
00:34:53.430 --> 00:34:57.784
Yet His Grace the King. it seems.
will not accept what his eyes see.

419
00:34:57.868 --> 00:34:59.786
This flimsy shield alone

420
00:34:59.870 --> 00:35:03.623
stands between you
and the headsman.

421
00:35:03.707 --> 00:35:06.726
The willful blindness of
a father towards his child.

422
00:35:06.810 --> 00:35:09.362
I wish my father affected
a similar blindness.

423
00:35:09.446 --> 00:35:12.298
Have I not these many years?

424
00:35:12.382 --> 00:35:14.300
And yet today.
you publicly assaulted

425
00:35:14.384 --> 00:35:18.204
a Knight of the Kings guard
in the. in the defense of your...

426
00:35:20.457 --> 00:35:23.860
You have your
honor and I have mine.

427
00:35:31.735 --> 00:35:33.970
To ease the pain.
Princess.

428
00:35:46.049 --> 00:35:48.968
- Thank you.
- You'll feel better in a day or two.

429
00:35:49.052 --> 00:35:50.787
when the milk dries up.

430
00:36:09.239 --> 00:36:11.224
My dear wife.

431
00:36:11.308 --> 00:36:13.126
Princess.

432
00:36:13.210 --> 00:36:16.480
Oh... I fell down.

433
00:36:18.215 --> 00:36:21.751
- Where have you been?
- Out with Qarl. Didn't I mention it?

434
00:36:23.520 --> 00:36:25.938
Are you in very much pain?

435
00:36:26.022 --> 00:36:27.940
The milk...

436
00:36:28.024 --> 00:36:30.343
- swells the breasts...
- Would you mind. Ser Qarl?

437
00:36:30.427 --> 00:36:32.178
I would like to speak
with my husband.

438
00:36:32.262 --> 00:36:34.030
Of course. Princess.

439
00:36:45.375 --> 00:36:47.393
War... is afoot again

440
00:36:47.477 --> 00:36:50.263
in the Step stones.
Rhaenyra.

441
00:36:50.347 --> 00:36:52.632
The Triarchy
takes new life

442
00:36:52.716 --> 00:36:55.701
from its alliance with Dorne.

443
00:36:55.785 --> 00:36:58.404
They're waylaying
ships and cargo.

444
00:36:58.488 --> 00:37:01.207
Qarl's been fighting there.
He showed me a...

445
00:37:04.227 --> 00:37:08.247
He showed me a sack of
sapphires big as walnuts

446
00:37:08.331 --> 00:37:11.050
he took from
the pirate he slew.

447
00:37:11.134 --> 00:37:13.753
Ahh... after all this time.

448
00:37:13.837 --> 00:37:16.189
this is just what I need.

449
00:37:16.273 --> 00:37:17.790
a little adventure.

450
00:37:17.874 --> 00:37:22.562
A good. honest battle
to enliven my blood again.

451
00:37:22.646 --> 00:37:25.298
He says there is
a Tyroshi general there.

452
00:37:25.382 --> 00:37:26.966
a giant. they say.

453
00:37:27.050 --> 00:37:31.904
who dyes his beard purple
and wears women's frocks.

454
00:37:35.625 --> 00:37:38.728
A few months. maybe... Hm.

455
00:37:42.332 --> 00:37:44.568
To be back at sea.

456
00:37:46.269 --> 00:37:48.855
Are you mad?

457
00:37:48.939 --> 00:37:51.624
Do you know
what's happened...

458
00:37:51.708 --> 00:37:53.659
while you've been guzzling
all the ale in Flea Bottom?

459
00:37:53.743 --> 00:37:56.462
Gods know what besides?

460
00:37:56.546 --> 00:37:58.965
Dark rumors are
hunting us. Laenor.

461
00:37:59.049 --> 00:38:00.900
They nip at our heels.

462
00:38:00.984 --> 00:38:06.739
Questions... about
our sons' parentage.

463
00:38:06.823 --> 00:38:10.243
Vile. disgusting
insinuations.

464
00:38:10.327 --> 00:38:12.345
Insinuations. are they?

465
00:38:12.429 --> 00:38:14.380
They are our sons!

466
00:38:14.464 --> 00:38:17.149
Yours and mine.

467
00:38:17.233 --> 00:38:19.519
And their true father
will not abandon them now

468
00:38:19.603 --> 00:38:21.888
to go carousing
through the Narrow Sea.

469
00:38:21.972 --> 00:38:25.775
- waggling his sword and winking at his sailors.
- I am a knight...

470
00:38:27.978 --> 00:38:29.896
and a warrior.

471
00:38:29.980 --> 00:38:35.585
And I have played
my part here. faithfully...

472
00:38:36.353 --> 00:38:40.406
for 10 years.

473
00:38:40.490 --> 00:38:44.243
- I am owed some...
- You are owed nothing!

474
00:38:44.327 --> 00:38:49.482
For 10 years. you have
indulged yourself at court.

475
00:38:49.566 --> 00:38:52.118
bought the finest horses.

476
00:38:52.202 --> 00:38:54.453
drunk the rarest of wines.

477
00:38:54.537 --> 00:38:56.088
fucked the lustiest boys.

478
00:38:56.172 --> 00:38:59.943
This was our agreement.
I have not begrudged you.

479
00:39:00.610 --> 00:39:01.845
But...

480
00:39:03.213 --> 00:39:07.600
you do not desert your post
when the storm lashes.

481
00:39:07.684 --> 00:39:12.622
The wise sailor flees
the storm as it gathers.

482
00:39:22.699 --> 00:39:25.168
Very well then.
I command you.

483
00:39:26.269 --> 00:39:28.588
As your Princess
and the heir to the throne.

484
00:39:28.672 --> 00:39:30.823
you are commanded to remain

485
00:39:30.907 --> 00:39:34.144
in King's Landing
and at my side.

486
00:39:54.597 --> 00:39:56.833
It's been eight years.
sweetling.

487
00:39:58.034 --> 00:40:01.237
- Half of them never do. you know?
- What?

488
00:40:04.140 --> 00:40:05.341
Hatch.

489
00:40:08.211 --> 00:40:09.946
Will they let me stay?

490
00:40:11.181 --> 00:40:13.232
Will who let you stay?

491
00:40:13.316 --> 00:40:15.051
The Prince of Pentos.

492
00:40:15.885 --> 00:40:17.821
I don't understand.

493
00:40:18.688 --> 00:40:20.924
He wants you and father...

494
00:40:22.192 --> 00:40:24.110
and Baela...

495
00:40:24.194 --> 00:40:26.129
'cause you have dragons.

496
00:40:30.233 --> 00:40:33.986
There is more than one way
to bind yourself to a dragon.

497
00:40:34.070 --> 00:40:38.724
I was without one
until I was 15 years old

498
00:40:38.808 --> 00:40:43.213
and now I ride Vhagar.
the largest in the world.

499
00:40:46.449 --> 00:40:48.300
You have a harder road.

500
00:40:48.384 --> 00:40:50.386
Baela's dragon was born to her.

501
00:40:52.789 --> 00:40:54.440
But if you wish to be a rider.

502
00:40:54.524 --> 00:40:57.727
you must claim that right.

503
00:40:58.995 --> 00:41:01.231
Your father would
tell you the same.

504
00:41:02.599 --> 00:41:04.701
Father ignores me.

505
00:41:10.874 --> 00:41:12.742
He's doing his best.

506
00:41:50.613 --> 00:41:52.849
Laenor has written.

507
00:41:53.917 --> 00:41:56.319
Rhaenyra has delivered
another son.

508
00:41:58.588 --> 00:42:00.039
Does your brother
mention if this one

509
00:42:00.123 --> 00:42:02.742
also bears a marked
but entirely coincidental

510
00:42:02.826 --> 00:42:05.311
resemblance to the
Commander of the City Watch?

511
00:42:05.395 --> 00:42:09.081
He seems
to have left that detail out.

512
00:42:09.165 --> 00:42:10.200
Mm.

513
00:42:11.868 --> 00:42:14.804
I miss my brother.
Daemon.

514
00:42:16.573 --> 00:42:18.408
As I think do you.

515
00:42:19.876 --> 00:42:23.529
I miss Westerosi
strong wine.

516
00:42:23.613 --> 00:42:27.217
It could be depended on for a
few hours of peaceful oblivion.

517
00:42:28.685 --> 00:42:31.254
This amber shit
that they drink here.

518
00:42:38.862 --> 00:42:41.080
Do you never long for home?

519
00:42:41.164 --> 00:42:42.281
No.

520
00:42:42.365 --> 00:42:45.017
- I don't believe you.
- Believe what you please.

521
00:42:45.101 --> 00:42:47.119
You laud the virtues
of Pentos.

522
00:42:47.203 --> 00:42:49.155
but you have
no interest in it.

523
00:42:49.239 --> 00:42:51.190
If you did. you would
venture into the city.

524
00:42:51.274 --> 00:42:53.192
but instead.
you spend your time here.

525
00:42:53.276 --> 00:42:55.294
in the library.
reading accounts

526
00:42:55.378 --> 00:42:58.831
of the same dead dragon lords
whose legacy you claim

527
00:42:58.915 --> 00:43:00.266
has no hold on you.

528
00:43:00.350 --> 00:43:02.701
Didn't know I was being
so minutely observed.

529
00:43:02.785 --> 00:43:07.323
- You do not sleep.
- Well. how can I with you haunting my every move?

530
00:43:10.393 --> 00:43:13.712
Life has. I know. disappointed you.

531
00:43:13.796 --> 00:43:16.515
Perhaps. I too. am not the wife
you would've wished for yourself.

532
00:43:16.599 --> 00:43:17.750
Laena.

533
00:43:17.834 --> 00:43:20.586
It does not pain me.

534
00:43:20.670 --> 00:43:22.906
I have made my peace.

535
00:43:26.342 --> 00:43:28.278
But you are more
than this. Daemon.

536
00:43:30.413 --> 00:43:33.566
The man I married
was more than this.

537
00:43:41.190 --> 00:43:43.442
It is Lord Blackwood's
contention. therefore.

538
00:43:43.526 --> 00:43:45.411
that the Brackens moved
the boundary stones

539
00:43:45.495 --> 00:43:46.745
in the dead of the night

540
00:43:46.829 --> 00:43:49.181
and put their horses
to graze in his field.

541
00:43:49.265 --> 00:43:51.717
Why was this issue
not brought before Lord Grover?

542
00:43:51.801 --> 00:43:55.054
Has he grown so feeble he
cannot settle a quarrel over rocks?

543
00:43:55.138 --> 00:43:57.256
I've heard
tale that Lord Grover's son

544
00:43:57.340 --> 00:43:59.625
now rules River run
in all but name.

545
00:43:59.709 --> 00:44:01.660
Well. he is also a Tully

546
00:44:01.744 --> 00:44:03.929
and this remains
a Tully problem.

547
00:44:04.013 --> 00:44:06.098
I would agree.

548
00:44:06.182 --> 00:44:08.701
- If we may move on. my lords...
- And yet.

549
00:44:08.785 --> 00:44:10.135
the Brackens
and the Black woods

550
00:44:10.219 --> 00:44:12.522
will use any excuse
to spill each other's blood.

551
00:44:15.458 --> 00:44:18.677
So... this dispute
bears looking into.

552
00:44:18.761 --> 00:44:22.848
There will be countryfolk who know where
the lines have been drawn for generations.

553
00:44:22.932 --> 00:44:24.434
That is easy enough.

554
00:44:25.501 --> 00:44:27.136
Of course.

555
00:44:29.272 --> 00:44:31.123
Ser Tyland.

556
00:44:31.207 --> 00:44:33.525
Uh. we should address

557
00:44:33.609 --> 00:44:36.462
the latest developments
in the Step stones. my lords.

558
00:44:36.546 --> 00:44:39.298
Will we ever be
shut of that blasted place?

559
00:44:39.382 --> 00:44:41.200
If you ask me. I think
the Black woods have

560
00:44:41.284 --> 00:44:42.668
- the upper hand.
- o.

561
00:44:42.752 --> 00:44:45.237
We've moved on to the
Step stones. Lord Beesbury.

562
00:44:45.321 --> 00:44:48.674
And the Triarchy's
new alliance with Dorne.

563
00:44:48.758 --> 00:44:53.312
I was hoping our negotiations with Sun
spear might persuade them to see reason.

564
00:44:53.396 --> 00:44:57.516
To trust a Martell
is to be disappointed.

565
00:44:57.600 --> 00:45:00.185
And where. I
wonder. is our Prince Daemon?

566
00:45:00.269 --> 00:45:02.821
Or I suppose I should call
him King. as he styled himself

567
00:45:02.905 --> 00:45:04.356
when he won
a battle there...

568
00:45:04.440 --> 00:45:06.191
- once.
- That was a decade ago

569
00:45:06.275 --> 00:45:08.260
and he has since left
the region undefended.

570
00:45:08.344 --> 00:45:10.095
We have
left it undefended.

571
00:45:10.179 --> 00:45:13.132
There should've been
fortifications built.

572
00:45:13.216 --> 00:45:15.067
watchtowers.
a fleet of ships.

573
00:45:15.151 --> 00:45:17.903
a garrison of soldiers
sent to hold our ground.

574
00:45:17.987 --> 00:45:19.389
We cannot afford it.

575
00:45:21.357 --> 00:45:25.277
Our coffers are great.
but not infinite.

576
00:45:25.361 --> 00:45:27.313
We must consider
the cost to our subjects.

577
00:45:27.397 --> 00:45:30.633
- I must agree.
- The cost of war is greater.

578
00:45:32.735 --> 00:45:37.340
But we have been lax and the
old monster now lifts its head.

579
00:45:42.512 --> 00:45:43.629
Let us be finished.

580
00:45:43.713 --> 00:45:46.449
Yes.

581
00:45:50.787 --> 00:45:51.787
Wait.

582
00:45:52.722 --> 00:45:54.457
I wish to speak.

583
00:45:55.625 --> 00:45:57.026
Be seated.

584
00:46:06.002 --> 00:46:09.205
I have felt the...

585
00:46:10.106 --> 00:46:12.224
strife...

586
00:46:12.308 --> 00:46:15.078
between our families
of late. my Queen.

587
00:46:17.346 --> 00:46:21.451
And for any offense given
by mine. I apologize.

588
00:46:23.286 --> 00:46:25.688
But we are one house.

589
00:46:26.689 --> 00:46:29.074
And long before that.

590
00:46:29.158 --> 00:46:30.660
we were friends.

591
00:46:36.666 --> 00:46:39.385
My son Jacaerys will inherit
the Iron Throne after me.

592
00:46:39.469 --> 00:46:42.705
I propose we betroth him
to your daughter. Helaena.

593
00:46:44.107 --> 00:46:46.725
Ally ourselves...

594
00:46:46.809 --> 00:46:49.094
once and for all.

595
00:46:49.178 --> 00:46:50.929
Let them rule together.

596
00:46:51.013 --> 00:46:53.749
A most judicious proposition.

597
00:46:57.854 --> 00:47:01.473
Additionally. if Syrax brings
forth another clutch of eggs.

598
00:47:01.557 --> 00:47:04.393
your son Aemond will have
his choice of them. uh...

599
00:47:05.328 --> 00:47:08.264
a symbol of our goodwill.

600
00:47:11.033 --> 00:47:12.568
Rhaenyra.

601
00:47:20.209 --> 00:47:23.179
Oh. Seven Hells. um.

602
00:47:25.114 --> 00:47:26.799
My dear...

603
00:47:26.883 --> 00:47:29.485
a dragon's egg
is a handsome gift.

604
00:47:30.920 --> 00:47:32.404
The King and I
thank you for your offer

605
00:47:32.488 --> 00:47:34.373
and we will consider it duly.

606
00:47:34.457 --> 00:47:36.692
You must rest now.
husband.

607
00:47:39.829 --> 00:47:41.397
Yes.

608
00:47:47.403 --> 00:47:49.288
How sweetly the fox speaks

609
00:47:49.372 --> 00:47:51.223
when it's been
cornered by the hounds.

610
00:47:51.307 --> 00:47:54.326
- She is sincere.
- She is desperate.

611
00:47:54.410 --> 00:47:56.562
She feels the earth
washing away beneath her feet

612
00:47:56.646 --> 00:47:59.098
and now she expects us
to ignore her transgressions

613
00:47:59.182 --> 00:48:00.933
and for me to marry
my only daughter

614
00:48:01.017 --> 00:48:02.568
to one of her...

615
00:48:02.652 --> 00:48:04.236
plain-featured sons.

616
00:48:04.320 --> 00:48:07.256
The proposal is
a good one. my Queen.

617
00:48:08.057 --> 00:48:09.508
We're a family.

618
00:48:09.592 --> 00:48:12.044
Let us put aside
these childish quarrels.

619
00:48:12.128 --> 00:48:15.481
Join hands
and be stronger for it.

620
00:48:15.565 --> 00:48:18.484
You may do
as you wish. husband...

621
00:48:18.568 --> 00:48:21.337
when I am cold
in my grave.

622
00:48:21.938 --> 00:48:23.172
Alicent.

623
00:48:24.941 --> 00:48:26.175
Alicent!

624
00:48:49.498 --> 00:48:51.734
I do not need the blanket...

625
00:48:55.104 --> 00:48:57.222
The Hand. Your Grace.

626
00:48:57.306 --> 00:49:00.543
- The King is resting.
- I will see him.

627
00:49:01.644 --> 00:49:02.845
Lean forward.

628
00:49:10.152 --> 00:49:13.505
I'm being endlessly
fussed over. Lyonel.

629
00:49:13.589 --> 00:49:16.525
It's a wonder I can
visit the privy alone.

630
00:49:17.093 --> 00:49:19.144
Your Grace.

631
00:49:19.228 --> 00:49:21.530
What might this errand
be about. Lord Lyonel?

632
00:49:24.200 --> 00:49:25.701
Your Grace. I feel...

633
00:49:27.937 --> 00:49:30.873
I have come to resign my
position as Hand of the King.

634
00:49:32.308 --> 00:49:34.026
The episode in the yard
this morning.

635
00:49:34.110 --> 00:49:36.929
My son Harwin
has disgraced himself

636
00:49:37.013 --> 00:49:40.165
and every fishwife in King's
Landing will soon be telling the tale.

637
00:49:40.249 --> 00:49:42.868
Young Harwin's outburst
was unfortunate.

638
00:49:42.952 --> 00:49:44.403
it's true.

639
00:49:44.487 --> 00:49:46.205
But he's been expelled
from the City Watch.

640
00:49:46.289 --> 00:49:47.573
That seems
punishment enough.

641
00:49:47.657 --> 00:49:50.426
Forgive me.
Your Grace. it is not.

642
00:49:57.266 --> 00:50:01.587
You have served me
faithfully for many years.

643
00:50:01.671 --> 00:50:02.938
10 as Hand.

644
00:50:04.340 --> 00:50:06.391
Your advice has been sage.

645
00:50:06.475 --> 00:50:09.161
unmarked by self-interest...

646
00:50:09.245 --> 00:50:12.315
which stands in contrast
to all others.

647
00:50:13.282 --> 00:50:15.017
You speak kind words...

648
00:50:16.218 --> 00:50:18.170
but there is a shadow
over my house

649
00:50:18.254 --> 00:50:20.405
and it grows... ever darker.

650
00:50:20.489 --> 00:50:23.426
I can no longer serve you
with integrity.

651
00:50:24.527 --> 00:50:26.462
What is this shadow?

652
00:50:27.496 --> 00:50:29.781
Name it. if it casts
such a gloom.

653
00:50:29.865 --> 00:50:34.804
Yes... we must have your
reasoning in plain language.

654
00:50:42.845 --> 00:50:44.046
I cannot.

655
00:50:45.881 --> 00:50:47.332
Then I cannot accept this.

656
00:50:47.416 --> 00:50:49.685
- My dear husband...
- I said no!

657
00:50:50.686 --> 00:50:54.039
- If you insist. my King.
- I do.

658
00:50:54.123 --> 00:50:56.341
You will continue in
your service to the crown.

659
00:50:58.894 --> 00:51:01.046
I would then ask leave
to take my son from court

660
00:51:01.130 --> 00:51:04.249
and escort him back to
the family seat at Harrenhal.

661
00:51:04.333 --> 00:51:06.318
He is my heir

662
00:51:06.402 --> 00:51:08.220
and will be lord of
Harren's castle one day.

663
00:51:08.304 --> 00:51:11.040
It is time he assumed
his duties there.

664
00:51:14.076 --> 00:51:15.311
Do it.

665
00:51:35.998 --> 00:51:38.067
Aren't you gonna help me?

666
00:52:17.373 --> 00:52:19.024
I took the liberty of beginning

667
00:52:19.108 --> 00:52:20.025
without you. Your Grace.

668
00:52:20.109 --> 00:52:23.095
It seemed a sin to let
such a pie grow cold.

669
00:52:23.179 --> 00:52:25.864
You did wisely. Lord Larys.

670
00:52:25.948 --> 00:52:28.600
Though you had no such worry
about the wine. surely.

671
00:52:28.684 --> 00:52:33.122
- Meat without wine is also a sin.
- Mm.

672
00:52:37.092 --> 00:52:39.778
It's been my duty to tell you
of happenings about the castle.

673
00:52:39.862 --> 00:52:43.682
but tonight you know.
and I do not.

674
00:52:43.766 --> 00:52:46.551
The King had an audience
with my father.

675
00:52:46.635 --> 00:52:48.537
He attempted
to resign his post.

676
00:52:49.338 --> 00:52:51.723
I thought as much.

677
00:52:51.807 --> 00:52:53.458
His honor's always
been a millstone

678
00:52:53.542 --> 00:52:55.778
about his esteemed neck.

679
00:52:57.646 --> 00:52:59.598
Interesting you said
"attempted"?

680
00:52:59.682 --> 00:53:02.801
My lord husband
refused to accept.

681
00:53:02.885 --> 00:53:06.838
Then he fell short of confessing
my brother's... transgressions.

682
00:53:06.922 --> 00:53:09.274
With his eruption in the yard.
your brother

683
00:53:09.358 --> 00:53:11.443
all but confessed
the truth himself.

684
00:53:11.527 --> 00:53:14.679
Truth has many flavors.
Your Grace.

685
00:53:14.763 --> 00:53:17.482
Do you expect the King to doom
his dear daughter to exile.

686
00:53:17.566 --> 00:53:20.002
or even...

687
00:53:21.103 --> 00:53:22.505
Talya. not now.

688
00:53:29.512 --> 00:53:32.964
It's a willful blindness.
the King.

689
00:53:33.048 --> 00:53:34.699
I mean. you'd surely
suffer the same affliction.

690
00:53:34.783 --> 00:53:37.019
- if it came to it.
- I would not.

691
00:53:38.654 --> 00:53:41.339
Lord Lyonel is to escort
Ser Harwin back to Harrenhal

692
00:53:41.423 --> 00:53:45.544
to watch over his seat whilst
he continues to serve as Hand.

693
00:53:45.628 --> 00:53:50.182
But the Hand is compromised
by the acts of his son.

694
00:53:50.266 --> 00:53:55.220
My father... cannot give
unbiased counsel to the King.

695
00:53:55.304 --> 00:53:58.723
It is now that I most rue the
absence of my own father.

696
00:53:58.807 --> 00:54:00.692
He wouldn't hesitate
to speak the truth to the King.

697
00:54:00.776 --> 00:54:02.194
If Otto High tower
were still Hand...

698
00:54:02.278 --> 00:54:04.996
You cannot say. my Queen.
that your father would be

699
00:54:05.080 --> 00:54:06.498
impartial in this matter.

700
00:54:06.582 --> 00:54:08.984
No. but he would
be partial to me!

701
00:54:18.093 --> 00:54:21.530
In all of King's Landing. is
there no one to take my side?

702
00:54:47.222 --> 00:54:50.826
What a collection
of heroes I have before me.

703
00:54:54.563 --> 00:54:56.948
A murderer...

704
00:54:57.032 --> 00:54:59.417
a deviant...

705
00:54:59.501 --> 00:55:01.987
a traitor to the crown.

706
00:55:02.071 --> 00:55:06.709
For your crimes. you've been
sentenced to death by hanging.

707
00:55:08.410 --> 00:55:10.646
What do you want with us?

708
00:55:13.515 --> 00:55:16.752
I am prepared
to offer you mercy...

709
00:55:18.020 --> 00:55:21.256
if you're prepared
to pay a little price.

710
00:55:45.114 --> 00:55:46.831
Push. my Lady.

711
00:55:46.915 --> 00:55:48.800
Push! Push!

712
00:55:48.884 --> 00:55:51.536
Push!

713
00:55:51.620 --> 00:55:54.356
- You must push!
Push!

714
00:55:56.091 --> 00:55:58.476
It needs to come now!

715
00:55:58.560 --> 00:55:59.962
Push!

716
00:56:01.964 --> 00:56:03.949
Push!

717
00:56:04.033 --> 00:56:06.351
You must push now. my Lady!

718
00:56:06.435 --> 00:56:09.321
Push!

719
00:56:27.056 --> 00:56:29.291
I've reached
the limit of my art.

720
00:56:31.160 --> 00:56:32.895
The child will not come.

721
00:56:35.464 --> 00:56:37.700
Ah. my brave girl.

722
00:56:42.838 --> 00:56:45.074
I am very sorry. my Prince.

723
00:56:46.341 --> 00:56:48.377
We could lay open the womb...

724
00:56:49.344 --> 00:56:51.496
try to remove the infant

725
00:56:51.580 --> 00:56:54.199
by way of the blade.

726
00:56:54.283 --> 00:56:57.502
But I cannot say
for a surety whether it lives.

727
00:56:57.586 --> 00:56:59.822
Would the mother survive it?

728
00:57:01.423 --> 00:57:03.158
No.

729
00:57:33.222 --> 00:57:36.458
<i>Speaks High Valyrian...</i>
Vhagar. dracarys.

730
00:57:38.293 --> 00:57:39.762
Agh!

731
00:57:40.863 --> 00:57:42.431
Dracarys!

732
00:57:44.833 --> 00:57:46.935
Dracarys!

733
00:57:50.739 --> 00:57:52.474
Dracarys.

734
00:57:53.242 --> 00:57:55.527
Dracarys!

735
00:57:57.346 --> 00:57:58.797
Dracarys.

736
00:58:19.468 --> 00:58:20.869
Laena!

737
00:58:43.392 --> 00:58:45.710
Be good to your mother. lads.

738
00:58:45.794 --> 00:58:47.529
I'll visit when I can.

739
00:58:50.866 --> 00:58:53.101
But that may be some time.

740
00:58:56.338 --> 00:58:57.539
Jace.

741
00:59:04.379 --> 00:59:05.948
I will return...

742
00:59:08.450 --> 00:59:10.052
I promise.

743
00:59:24.466 --> 00:59:28.620
I will be a stranger
when we meet again.

744
00:59:45.687 --> 00:59:47.022
Princess.

745
01:00:08.877 --> 01:00:11.429
We will exchange letters
by raven.

746
01:00:11.513 --> 01:00:15.484
- Won't that be fun?
- Is Harwin Strong my father?

747
01:00:19.554 --> 01:00:21.290
Am I a bastard?

748
01:00:25.727 --> 01:00:27.963
You are a Targaryen.

749
01:00:29.431 --> 01:00:31.166
That's all that matters.

750
01:00:55.624 --> 01:00:56.658
A word?

751
01:01:03.532 --> 01:01:05.133
I take it he's gone.

752
01:01:07.235 --> 01:01:09.271
We're finished here.
We're leaving.

753
01:01:12.007 --> 01:01:14.893
What of your offer?
Jace and Helaena?

754
01:01:14.977 --> 01:01:17.395
I have been undermined...

755
01:01:17.479 --> 01:01:20.832
and made a spectacle. They
whisper about me in the corridors.

756
01:01:20.916 --> 01:01:23.485
Well. I leave them to it.

757
01:01:27.189 --> 01:01:29.474
To Dragons tone then?

758
01:01:29.558 --> 01:01:31.293
We should've left years ago.

759
01:01:36.965 --> 01:01:38.583
What of your position?

760
01:01:38.667 --> 01:01:41.052
You've always said if you
were absent from court.

761
01:01:41.136 --> 01:01:44.789
she would pour her honey
in your father's ear.

762
01:01:44.873 --> 01:01:48.276
The wise sailor flees
the storm as it gathers.

763
01:01:49.311 --> 01:01:51.546
Laenor...

764
01:01:53.348 --> 01:01:55.017
bring him.

765
01:01:56.385 --> 01:01:58.954
We'll need every sword
we can muster.

766
01:03:15.130 --> 01:03:18.649
Fire! I will burn!

767
01:03:18.733 --> 01:03:21.486
Harwin!
Ah! Harwin!

768
01:03:45.660 --> 01:03:50.098
What are children. but a weakness?

769
01:03:53.001 --> 01:03:54.736
A folly?

770
01:03:55.837 --> 01:03:57.772
A futility?

771
01:04:02.677 --> 01:04:04.996
Through them.
you imagine you cheat

772
01:04:05.080 --> 01:04:08.517
the great darkness
of its victory.

773
01:04:23.365 --> 01:04:28.637
You will persist forever.
in some form or another.

774
01:04:31.206 --> 01:04:34.525
As if they will keep
you from the dust.

775
01:04:45.587 --> 01:04:47.338
But for them...

776
01:04:47.422 --> 01:04:50.358
you surrender
what you should not.

777
01:04:52.761 --> 01:04:56.781
You may know what is
the right thing to be done.

778
01:04:56.865 --> 01:05:00.468
but... love stays the hand.

779
01:05:09.110 --> 01:05:10.512
Love...

780
01:05:12.581 --> 01:05:14.616
is a downfall.

781
01:05:19.354 --> 01:05:23.625
Best to make your way
through life unencumbered...

782
01:05:24.759 --> 01:05:26.661
if you ask me.

783
01:05:29.731 --> 01:05:30.748
They're dead.

784
01:05:30.832 --> 01:05:34.269
You've heard the stories
of Harrenhal. Your Grace.

785
01:05:35.604 --> 01:05:37.800
It was built in hubris
by Harren the Black

786
01:05:37.885 --> 01:05:40.191
as a monument
to his own greatness.

787
01:05:40.275 --> 01:05:43.511
Blood mixed into the mortar.

788
01:05:45.447 --> 01:05:48.432
It is said to be
a cursed place.

789
01:05:48.516 --> 01:05:52.537
That it passes judgment on
all who pass beneath its gates.

790
01:05:52.621 --> 01:05:54.105
You...

791
01:05:54.189 --> 01:05:56.424
You passed judgment.

792
01:05:57.892 --> 01:05:59.461
The Queen makes a wish.

793
01:06:00.929 --> 01:06:04.933
What servant of the realm
would not strive to fulfill it?

794
01:06:06.635 --> 01:06:10.572
I assume you will write
to your father now?

795
01:06:12.507 --> 01:06:13.541
Larys...

796
01:06:14.442 --> 01:06:16.911
I did not wish for this.

797
01:06:18.890 --> 01:06:22.711
I feel certain
you will reward me...

798
01:06:24.643 --> 01:06:26.547
when the time is right.

798
01:06:27.305 --> 01:07:27.626
